    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\n**7 files to touch, in order:**\n\n### New files\n1. **`src/interchange/ini.zig`** — Self-contained line-by-line INI parser. No lexer needed. Produces an `Expr` AST (nested `E.Object` with `E.String` values). Supports `[sections]`, `key=value` / `key: value`, `;`/`#` comments (full-line and inline). All allocation goes through the arena passed in.\n\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — JS wrapper. `parse` follows `TOMLObject.zig` exactly (arena + `ASTMemoryAllocator` + `printJSON` + `toJSByParseJSON`). `stringify` walks the JSValue directly (no Expr needed): emits global flat keys first, then `[section]` blocks for object-valued keys.\n\n3. **`test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts`** — Tests for both `parse` and `stringify`, covering sections, comments, both separator styles (`=` and `:`), whitespace trimming, and inline comment stripping.\n\n### Edited files\n4. **`src/interchange.zig`** — Add `pub const ini = @import(\"./interchange/ini.zig\");`\n5. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n6. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — 4 small edits: lazy property declaration, getter function, `exportAll()` entry, and import alias — all mirroring the YAML/TOML entries exactly.\n7. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` after the YAML namespace.",
